HEADWORD: Structured
<hw>Struc"tured</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Having a definite organic structure; showing differentiation of
parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The passage from a structureless state to a <qex>structured</qex>
state is itself a vital process.</q> <rj><qau>H. Spencer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Structureless</ent>⟦br⟧
